com.inqwell.any

Interface Process

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Any, Composite, Map, Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractProcess, AnyClient.ClientUserProcess, BasicProcess, ClientMonitor, DeadlockScanner, IoProcess, LockerProxy, ProxyProcess, SerializedProcess, ServerListener, ServerMonitor, UserProcess

    public interface Process
extends Map
    Executables in the Any environment. All known implementations start their own thread.

        void setWaitingObject(Any a,
                      long timeout)
        Set the object this Process is waiting for notification on and the timeout it is willing to wait for.
        Parameters:
        a - the object or null if this process is no longer waiting.
        timeout - the length of time the process is willing to wait or zero if not waiting.

      • setLockWaitObject

        void setLockWaitObject(Any a,
                       long timeout)
        Set the object this Process is waiting to acquire the lock for and the timeout it is willing to wait for the lock to become available.
        Parameters:
        a - the object or null if this process is no longer waiting for the lock.
        timeout - the length of time the process is willing to wait or zero if not waiting.

      • getWaitingObject

        Any getWaitingObject()
        Return the object this process is waiting for notification on or null if the process is not waiting for notification.

      • getWaitingTimeout

        long getWaitingTimeout()
        Return the timeout that that is running against the object this process is waiting for notification on.
        Returns:
        -1 if waiting indefinitely, non-zero if waiting for a finite time or zero if not currently waiting

      • getLockWaitObject

        Any getLockWaitObject()
        Return the object this process is waiting to acquire the lock on or null if this process is not currently waiting for a lock. A lock may be implicit (taken out as required by the system) or explicit (taken out by the user). Explicit locks may be temporarily relinquished if the locking process chooses to wait on a locked object for notification from another process.

      • getLockWaitTimeout

        long getLockWaitTimeout()
        Return the timeout that that is running against the object this process is waiting to acquire the lock for.
        Returns:
        -1 if waiting indefinitely, non-zero if waiting for a finite time or zero if not currently waiting
